text: Are you totally or partially unemployed for no fault of your own?

text: Are you physically able to work, available for work, and ready and willing to accept work immediately?

text: Are you unable to do your regular or customary work?

text: Have you lost wages due to the need to provide care for a seriously ill family member, help after the deployment of a family member or to bond with a new child?

text: Were you employed or actively looking for work at the time your family leave began?

text: Has it been less than 41 days since your family leave began?

text: Do you own, rent or otherwise live in a home?

name: resouces_2
text: Do you currently recieve benefits from any of these programs?

name: resources_3
text: Do you have less than $10,000 in cash, bank accounts and other resources ($15,000 if disabled or 60 years or older)

name: resouces_4
text: Do you have resources less than $2,000 for an individual or $3,000 for a couple?

name: long_term_care_1
text: Are you receiving or expected to receive care for at least 30 days after the month of admission in a Hospital, Skilled Nursing Facility, Intermediate Care Facility (ICF) or a Convalescent Home?

name: willing_to_do_1
text: If you have filed income taxes, are you willing to declare your tax filing status?

name: willing_to_do_2
text: Are you willing to participate in Welfare-to-Work activities?
